The paper discusses a parametric framework for process calculi and gives a new operational semantics to psi-calculi. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses mechanised proofs of standard algebraic and congruence properties of bisimilarity, which is a topic that falls under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the encoding of mixed choice under strong quality criteria, which is a topic that falls under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the limitations of psi-calculi and how they can be lifted, which is a topic that falls under the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the correspondence with a reduction semantics and barbed bisimulation, which is a topic that falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
